<i>noun</i>: 치장 [치장], 차림새 [차림새], 몸치장 [몸치장], 몸단장 [몸단장], 모양 [모양] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>치장 [치장]</dt><br>
<dd>decoration; grooming</dd><br>
<dd>잘 매만져 곱게 꾸밈.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of adorning the appearance of someone or something.</dd><br>
<dt>차림새 [차림새]</dt><br>
<dd>appearance; grooming</dd><br>
<dd>꾸미고 갖추어서 차린 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>The aspect in which one grooms the face, body, etc., or does something carefully.</dd><br>
<dt>몸치장 [몸치장]</dt><br>
<dd>preening; grooming</dd><br>
<dd>옷, 화장, 액세서리 등으로 몸을 보기 좋게 꾸밈.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of making oneself look attractive by dressing up and wearing make-up, accessories, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>몸단장 [몸단장]</dt><br>
<dd>grooming</dd><br>
<dd>옷, 화장, 액세서리 등으로 몸을 보기 좋게 꾸밈.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of making oneself look good with clothes, make-up, accessories, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>모양 [모양]</dt><br>
<dd>1. shape</dd><br>
<dd>겉으로 나타나는 생김새나 모습.</dd><br>
<dd>The outer appearance or aspect.</dd><br>
<dd>2. grooming</dd><br>
<dd>얼굴이나 몸 등을 보기 좋게 꾸미는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of grooming the face, body, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>3. state; condition</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 형편이나 상태, 또는 일이 돌아가는 상황.</dd><br>
<dd>A situation or condition, or the state of an affair.</dd><br>
<dd>4. appearance</dd><br>
<dd>남에게 보이거나 비추어지는 모습.</dd><br>
<dd>The aspect that is visible or shown to others.</dd><br>
<dd>5. shape</dd><br>
<dd>무엇과 같거나 비슷한 모습.</dd><br>
<dd>An appearance that matches or resembles something.</dd><br>
<dd>6. way</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 방식이나 방법.</dd><br>
<dd>A way or method.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>